I think it would be very useful to have the ability to set the name attribute of inputs in filters (I am using Tablesorter with ajax calls). I think this could be set like this (similar to initialization of values):

`<th data-name='my_name_attribute'>Field 1</th>`

I just made some tests in _jquery.tablesorter.widgets.js_, the code below does the job but that is probably not the cleanest way to achieve it.

```
buildFilter = $( '<input type="search">' ).appendTo( $filter );

/* My modification is below: */
if ($(table).find('thead tr:first th').eq(column).data('name') != undefined) {
	buildFilter.attr('name', $(table).find('thead tr:first th').eq(column).data('name'));
}
```

Thanks

Using a well formatted PPT template, I tried to replace a string within all existing components to get a well formatted customized presentation.

The text replacement worked fine, but the **formatting was quite damaged making the PPT unusable for a  presentation**. Is there a way to avoid damaging the formatting while replaceing the text placeholders? 

Here the method I used to do the replacement:

```
for slide in ppt.slides:
    for shape in slide.shapes:
        if shape.has_text_frame:
            shape.text = shape.text.replace(   search_str    ,    repl_str    )
```

